      <title>Peter Carey: "The Chemistry of Tears"</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<p>Australian author Peter Carey is one of only two novelists to win the prestigious Booker Prize twice. He is nothing if not prolific. Over the course of his 40-year career he has written 12 novels, a collection of short stories, numerous essays, a travelogue and two screenplays. Every new book is eagerly awaited by his multitude of fans around the world, who are drawn by his quirky characters and unlikely pairings. His latest book, "The Chemistry of Tears," is no exception--it's a romance of the mind across time and technology.</p>]]></description>
